Package: fibr
Type: Package
Title: Holonomy Diagnostics for Hierarchical MCMC
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Aidan D", "Bindoff",
           email   = "aidan.bindoff@utas.edu.au",
           role    = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-0943-2702"))
Description: Detects non-trivial holonomy in Markov chain Monte Carlo chains
    from hierarchical models by exploiting the fiber bundle structure of the
    joint parameter space. The Fisher information metric on the total space
    induces a connection whose curvature produces a rotation of local
    (fiber) parameters when global (base space) hyperparameters traverse closed
    loops. This geometric obstruction to mixing is invisible to standard
    diagnostics such as R-hat, effective sample size, and divergence counts.
